@graham_what I was drawn to this shot the moment I saw it. Just a fantastic moment captured and this is also my latest piece purchased. Hope you enjoyed reading https://t.co/6Kmyxypdk6
@astromarkc1 Space is awesome. I really enjoy Mark's art and seeing him improve in what is an extremely challenging genre of photography https://t.co/IqCm73TSha
@James_MPhoto What else is there to say about this shot but WOW!!! Peyto lake is stunning during the day let alone seeing it with the aurora dancing above https://t.co/L5aFn5f2dy
@lance_wilson_ I love this shot from Lance. I really enjoy how the light trails get covered by the fog. Adds a sense of mystery to the photo https://t.co/YolqTYDCZq
@jsaragossaNFT I love how even photographing smoke can create such a beautiful abstract piece of art. https://t.co/DoUlanzrHj
@sarahlyndsay_ makes appearance no.3. I love the landscape here and the pose of the dress really helps with the drama of the sky. https://t.co/tI43hP4UUx
@tristan_todd_ makes another appearance. This shot is just incredible. The drama of the atmosphere really gets me going. The story of this Yukon trip is exhilarating https://t.co/qCctTxqcSU
@dyptre I love this shot. The trunk really leads your eye into the image and gives depth. For a messy scene it's well composed. Love the shutter speed for the water too https://t.co/39LnTHiuuO

@LokiHighlock This is such an intriguing shot. The lilly isolated by everything else with the light, really draws your eye in. I like the editing done on this one. Initially I thought it was done under the moon light but is in fact sunlight. https://t.co/mmr4kLTkf2
@Matdphoto What else is there to say about this epic NZ landscape? The light on top of the mountain in the background is *chefs kiss https://t.co/CuaIBPLhKg
@russimages Lampman is iconic. Such an incredible self portrait series from Russ. It's unique and it also makes me laugh when I look at it. I hope lampman's date went well. https://t.co/h7rfQZGIXk
@avinashpc6 I mentioned it last week but I'll say it again this is such a fantastic shot. I love all the detail captured in the eyes of this dragonfly. https://t.co/eOjmuyByOH

@justjuliasky This might be my favourite shot in my whole collection. The eeriness of the whole photo is perfect. The graffiti on the statue is the cherry on top. I love the idea of exploring abandoned themeparks. I can still hear the laughter of children roaming it. https://t.co/6ciWO3JCI1

@sbedaux I asked one night for a photo that would make me utter the words what the fuck. This shot of a drunken luchador did just that. It's another shot that unsettles me in a good way and I like art that challenges me https://t.co/bNekUA1hH8

@cabionur A great street photography shot that really unsettles me in a good way. The combination of the face paint which gives off a creepy vibe and then the rose appears as a gift to draw you in. I'm really not sure what will happen if I take it. Get's my imagination going. https://t.co/G5Kd5YW6Zm

@ShutterCapital This jelly fish shot is so eerie yet beautiful at the same time. I saw this on the OS trending page and it really captivated me. I never considered jellyfish to be photogenic but I was proven wrong. https://t.co/8TaGxSLRKh

@EBleicher There is a reason why Eric has appeared again. I love the shape of this aurora and the no foreground. It allows me to just fully immerse myself into it and as the title of the piece suggests.

Breathe. https://t.co/IUX6XLRlke
@sarahlyndsay_ Another shot From Sarah that is so epic and moody. Big fan of the long exposure of the clouds. https://t.co/0fzAnYs6Ik

@sarahlyndsay_ I've been following Sarah and her self portrait work on instagram for a long time. I love the background in this. The painted rocks give the photo so much to look at. https://t.co/qc5GAWEBDM
@Prasanthdasds I love the ferocity in the eyes of this Cheetah. I can just feel it staring into my soul. That post feeding look really shows the brutality of the wild. https://t.co/ugwAcA4rNU

@vastdepth I like trees, I like the milky-way. I couoldn't not add this to my collection. I really love how Venus is cradled in the tree. Great framing. Another thing that I like is the time it has been shot. Nautical Twilight. Very rare to see that from astro photographers. https://t.co/XV1AielcmK

@hauglandphoto Another beautiful scene. The water looks so inviting, the sun beaming through the trees. It truly gives the feeling of life. Ole showed me what this spot looks like in Winter. I'll take Spring every day https://t.co/nRdPcmeEBd

@tristan_todd_ Tristan might be more known for his rainforest work but his backcountry landscape shots are a sight to behold. I love this one. A landscape very alien to me and so dramatic. This won't be the only inclusion of the Yukon https://t.co/6CiV1qK1r0
@DocCraftAlot It's a very dreamy and calm looking photo. Very ethereal. https://t.co/mMzEnEOxWs

@debc_nz I've tried making interesting sand shots myself and can never really pull it off. Kudos to Deb for pulling that off here. I have fun following the curves in the sand to draw my eye around the frame https://t.co/F0GQrSBWIP

@AmberArtStudio As I stated last week I was drawn to the cause of helping save these giant trees but I also love the juxtaposition of the sapling and the mature tree. It's almost like a glimpse into the future https://t.co/aBPN0o0uep
@CodyBakerrrr This shot has it all. Burner sky, epic foreground, impressive mountains. It's a landscape photographers wet dream. I've got a real soft spot for Canada as well. https://t.co/NB7OejQoR7

@realflyingkiwi This shot reminded me of my Fiancee. Her favourite animal being an Orca. I had to add this into my collection. It's a unique shot as well. Don't see too many Orca shots from this angle. https://t.co/XdVUU3guTW

@luke_lens The atmosphere in this shot I love. The falling snow being caught in the street light. The desolate and lonely feeling I get from an empty street. It's just a really beautiful shot. https://t.co/o4YKXNIj7D

@AndrewHookerPh1 I love this shot from Andrew. As I said to him when I first bought this piece, It made me think of a prehistoric Australia, when megafauna roamed. It really got my imagination going. https://t.co/tIh3hfilS4
